50|$|If the {{electrons}} emit a <b>light</b> <b>wave</b> {{which is in}} phase with the <b>light</b> <b>wave</b> shaking them, it will amplify the <b>light</b> <b>wave.</b> This is rare, but occurs in lasers due to stimulated emission. It corresponds to an imaginary index of refraction, with the opposite sign to that of absorption.|$|R
