50|$|If the {{electrons}} emit a <b>light</b> <b>wave</b> which is 90° {{out of phase}} with the <b>light</b> <b>wave</b> shaking them, it will cause the total <b>light</b> <b>wave</b> to travel slower. This is the normal refraction of transparent materials like glass or water, and corresponds to a refractive index which is real and greater than 1.|$|R
